pageContext.claim: “Wow, Report Just Out! Google manipulated from 2.6 million to 16 million votes for Hillary Clinton in 2016 Election! This was put out by a Clinton supporter, not a Trump Supporter! Google should be sued. My victory was even bigger than thought!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is referring to a disputed estimate given by Robert Epstein, a psychologist and former editor in chief at Psychology Today, who examined how Google Search might have influenced undecided voters in the 2016 election by providing more positive results for one candidate than the other. In an interview with The New York Times, Epstein disputed Trump’s characterization of his work. “I've never said Google manipulated the 2016 elections,” he said. “The range of numbers he listed in the tweet is also incorrect.”
